President Jacob Zuma has paid a courtesy visit to the ailing founder and leader of the multi-Grammy Award winning group Ladysmith Black Mambazo in Ladysmith, in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands.Professor Joseph Shabalala retired from active music after he became sick. The presidential visit was in honour of Shabalala and his group&#8217;s role in putting South Africa and scathamiya music on the global map.KwaZulu-Natal premier, Willies Mchunu and the MECs of Sports and Recreation and Arts and Culture accompanied President Zuma.Ladysmith Black Mambazo has won four Grammy Awards, and collaborated with a number of accomplished international musicians and bands such as Paul Simon, Andreas Vollenweider, Oliver Mtukudzi and Sitimela.-SABC